answers.body_markdown:
Possible, but with limitations.  

Because records are immutable, [constructor-mapping](https://mybatis.org/mybatis-3/sqlmap-xml.html#constructor) must be used.  
And, to pass a `Collection` to a constructor, you have to use [nested select](https://mybatis.org/mybatis-3/sqlmap-xml.html#nested-select-for-collection).  
This means that if you are trying to retrieve N parent records, N+1 SELECTs will be executed.

If the N+1 problem is a blocker, you may have to use POJOs and convert them into records in the service layer or in a default method of the mapper interface.

Here is a simple example.  
If this is too simple to apply to your project, please add more details to the question.

```sql
create table item (
  id int primary key,
  name varchar(10)
);

create table prop (
  id int primary key,
  url varchar(100),
  item_id int
)
```

```java
@Results(id = &quot;propertyRM&quot;)
@Arg(id = true, column = &quot;id&quot;, javaType = int.class)
@Arg(column = &quot;url&quot;, javaType = String.class)
@Select(&quot;select id, url from prop where item_id = #{itemId}&quot;)
Collection&lt;Property&gt; selectProperties(Integer itemId);

@Arg(id = true, column = &quot;id&quot;, javaType = Integer.class)
@Arg(javaType = Collection.class,  select = &quot;selectProperties&quot;, column = &quot;id&quot;)
@Select(&quot;select id, name from item&quot;)
List&lt;Item&gt; selectItems();
```

Here is an equivalent XML version:

```xml
&lt;resultMap id=&quot;propertyRM&quot; type=&quot;pkg.Property&quot;&gt;
  &lt;constructor&gt;
    &lt;idArg column=&quot;id&quot; javaType=&quot;int&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;arg column=&quot;url&quot; javaType=&quot;string&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/constructor&gt;
&lt;/resultMap&gt;

&lt;resultMap id=&quot;itemRM&quot; type=&quot;pkg.Item&quot;&gt;
  &lt;constructor&gt;
    &lt;idArg column=&quot;id&quot; javaType=&quot;int&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;arg column=&quot;name&quot; javaType=&quot;string&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;arg javaType=&quot;java.util.Collection&quot;
      select=&quot;selectProperties&quot; column=&quot;id&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/constructor&gt;
&lt;/resultMap&gt;

&lt;select id=&quot;selectProperties&quot; resultMap=&quot;propertyRM&quot;&gt;
  select id, url from prop where item_id = #{itemId}
&lt;/select&gt;

&lt;select id=&quot;selectItems&quot; resultMap=&quot;itemRM&quot;&gt;
  select id, name from prop
&lt;/select&gt;
```

Note that the `Collection` passed to the constructor is mutable, so if you want &quot;deeply immutable&quot; records, you may have to implement the constructor explicitly.

